# FABER Workflow Framework

This project uses the `fractary-faber` CLI and skills for SDLC workflow management.

## Skills

Skills are in `plugins/faber/skills/*/SKILL.md`. Read the relevant skill for detailed guidance.

Key skills:
- `fractary-faber-workflow-plan` — Plan workflows for work items
- `fractary-faber-workflow-runner` — Execute FABER workflows
- `fractary-faber-config-manager` — Initialize/update/validate configuration
- `fractary-faber-run-inspector` — Inspect workflow run status
- `fractary-faber-workflow-author` — Create/update workflow definitions

## CLI

Run `fractary-faber --help` for full usage. Key commands:
- `fractary-faber workflow-plan --work-id <ids>` — plan workflows
- `fractary-faber workflow-run --work-id <ids>` — execute workflows
- `fractary-faber config init|update|validate` — manage configuration
- `fractary-faber runs verify-complete <run-id>` — verify run completion
- `fractary-faber run-inspect <id>` — inspect workflow status

## Configuration

Configuration is at `.fractary/config.yaml`. Run `fractary-faber config init` to set up.
